namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Hello guys.
This is Himanshu here from On Print Shop.

I am Senior Web 2 print consultant and today I am going to give you a brief demo on offline order management through On Print Shop, which has helped many clients to have fast order processing by 80% and increased report orders up to 60%.
But before I move on to this small presentation, I would like to ask those PSPS who are watching this particular presentation specifically the three questions.
First, do you receive orders through walk insurance emails, calls?
Secondly, do you invest same time and money for new Oregon reorder?
And the third and the most important question, how do you know your customers ordering pattern, their product purchasing pattern?

So to answer the all of this question on print shop has come up with three easy steps where PSP's can increase repeat orders and reduce the operation cost very easily by adding as many customers as they want through the admin panel.
Place orders on behalf of customers.
Thirdly, customers PSP team can easily reorder the same configuration.

Now let me take a real time case scenario where one of the client has given an order of business cards with 2000 quantity and some attributes option and as put up a comment I will pick up the same from your store.
But please make it this ready before 8th of July and.
Hint client has uploaded the file called order.
Now what your staff will do they will come back to the admin panel.
Once again this is printers admin panel of on print shop.
They will come to the add new order section.

You have two things either you can add customers new by filling up the basic details which will get stored into the system automatically or otherwise if you have uploaded the list of your clients through excel file which is called mass import then the system will capture the details automatically.
Let's say if I write Himanshu system will capture me the details.
Here the details are captured again.
If I click next system will ask me whether there is an existing digital catalog which I have prepared or is there any custom product which client has has some requirement.
Now let's say if I already have a product catalog, so I will select certain product.
So I have 2 into 3.5 as the basic.
Now here you have two options either you can manually put up the details automatically or secondly we have a pre configured and predefined attributes made for all the products.
So you can choose anyone of them and the system will give you instant estimate.
Let's say if I say spot UV round and if I apply all the options, the system will capture all the details.
The most important part, uploading the file.
As soon as your staff has uploaded the file, they have two options.
One they can either add another product to the cart and put up the order, or maybe they can just go and save and continue.
Now once this save and continue the system will ask them to have shipping method and the payment method.
So right now you have two options where start your client will be picking up local.
So either you can choose local pickup from store.
If and if they want to get shipped these their products wanted to be shipped then they can select expedite and payment.
Since they are already on in front of you, they can.
You can choose a POS and enter a transaction ID and confirm the order.
Now this is your confirmed order.
Now the solution will generate the invoice automatically for you once your order is confirmed.
So for this order, if I have to generate the invoice, system will generate the invoice automatically for me.
This is your invoice with whatever options I have put forward and all the details of customer shipping, billing and pay mail details are captured.
Your staff or your customers can reorder the same configuration again.
So I'm coming back to the printers admin panel again here in the webs in the your, your staff can come up in the customer order section.
They can simply login as a customer and put the order on your behalf.
Now as a next step, your client would probably come on to your public storefront, will have their own credentials and login into their own my account section.
This is the public store account.
They would be seen with all the orders, the recent orders, portfolio and everything.
Now once they go into the order section and if they want to reorder the same configuration, they can click reorder, continue, add their own comments.
They can choose either pay on pay on account status if it is an existing client or if the normal way of paying that is online payment is made if a client is making the payment online, right?
And as a next step, they can select the shipping type that is Chicago and complete the order.
Now this is your confirmed order.
Now once your order is confirmed and the reorder has been given you, your staff and all the PSP's can find customer ordering patterns for proactive business strategies.
And this can happen very easily with our solution where if we go into the printers admin panel once again into into the on print shop, you will find the report section.
Where will you find the customer section?
You can generate customer order summary wherever you have lots and lots of filters.
Let's say if I want to generate a report for this year and show the report.

So this will generate me the customer details, the number of orders they have placed, what is the number, number of orders, the value of orders that has been given, the tax, shipping discount total and everything.
And you can export this file into the OMATA and run and targeted campaign for them as well.
Similarly, when you talk about customer details, you may find it out there are hundreds of filters which are there.
Let's say if there is order greater than 250 and I set up a date of September 4th to till this date and show the report, you would find only those reports which have orders more than 259.
So, so these have login count 6.
These have login count 7.
What what is the registered date?
What are the customer details?
How many orders?
What is the value of the order they have given.
So all these order who has a value of more than 250 are being shown here.
So you can earn a mass targeted campaign for your for your client.
In a similar way, one of our clients rapid painting did the same thing where they reached the point of 90% reduction even labor required for order processing where what they did.
First of all, they transferred all the existing products using the mass CSV of their clients, which enables them to send the e-mail and SMS notifications.
Once those clients were getting e-mail and SMS notifications, they gradually started ordering.
And what happens when their clients started ordering, their team got freed and instead they started working on new customers.
And today they have more than 7 to 8 B to B customers and moving ahead with us and one of the most profound solution provider with on print shop.
Thank you very much.
